title: module 'deeplabcut' has no attribute 'train_network'
body:
hello！The following error occurred when I ran demo.py

import deeplabcut
task='rong1'
experimenter='hhui'
video='F:\DeepLabCut-master\examples\\reachingvideo1.avi'
path_config_file=deeplabcut.create_new_project(task,experimenter,video, working_directory='F:\DeepLabCut-master\examples',copy_videos=True)
deeplabcut.extract_frames(path_config_file,'automyatic','uniform',crop=True)
deeplabcut.label_frames(path_config_file)
deeplabcut.check_labels(path_config_file)
deeplabcut.create_training_dataset(path_config_file)
deeplabcut.train_network(path_config_file)
deeplabcut.evaluate_network(path_config_file)
videofile_path ='F:\DeepLabCut-master\examples\\reachingvideo1.avi'
deeplabcut.analyze_videos(path_config_file,videofile_path)
deeplabcut.create_labeled_video(path_config_file,videofile_path)
deeplabcut.plot_trajectories(path_config_file,videofile_path)

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "F:/DeepLabCut-master/demo_objdata.py", line 10, in <module>
    deeplabcut.train_network(path_config_file)
AttributeError: module 'deeplabcut' has no attribute 'train_network'
But I can find this script in training.py，And there are a lot of similar operations that can't be imported later.
I look forward to your reply!thanks!
